# ESP32 UART Communication (ESP-IDF)

## Overview

This project demonstrates basic UART communication on the ESP32 using ESP-IDF and FreeRTOS.
The code sends the message `"Hello Pakistan"` repeatedly every second over UART0.

## Features

* UART0 initialization with baud rate 115200
* Sending strings via UART0
* Periodic transmission with FreeRTOS `vTaskDelay()`
* Uses default TX/RX pins of UART0 (USB serial connection)

## Requirements

* ESP32 Development Board
* ESP-IDF (v5.x or later)
* PlatformIO / VS Code (recommended)

## Usage

1. Clone this repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/esp32-uart-demo.git
   ```
2. Open the project in PlatformIO or ESP-IDF environment.
3. Build and flash to your ESP32:

   ```bash
   idf.py build flash monitor
   ```
4. Open the serial monitor to see the output.

## Pin Configuration

Using **UART0 (default USB serial)**:

* TX → USB TX (default)
* RX → USB RX (default)

No extra wiring needed when connected via USB.

## Example Output

When monitored over UART:

Hello Pakistan
Hello Pakistan
Hello Pakistan
``

